WrapLabel.getMinimumSize() does the following: Dimension d = getEllipseTextSize().intersect(getTextExtents(getText(), f, getMapMode().DPtoLP(FigureUtilities.getFontMetrics(f).getHeight())));
Calling intersect() will cause the ellipseTextSize to be updated which doesn't make sense. This can then lead to an incorrect minimum size being returned.
The solution is to use getIntersected() instead of intersects().

