I would like to show the following text in a cheat sheet step:

public static void main(String[] args) {
   if (foo()) {
      bar();
   }
}

So here's what I entered in the editor for the step body:

public static void main(String[] args) {<br/>
   if (foo()) {<br/>
      bar();<br/>
   }<br/>
}<br/>

It works, but if I close and reopen the editor, then it reformats it to this:

public static void main(String[] args) {<br/> if (foo()) {<br/> bar();<br/> }<br/>}<br/>

Which is hard to read or edit. So it's actually harder in the editor than in the raw XML. Would it be possible to preserve the formatting?
